    chdir c:\\public\\jones
    copy c:*.* d:\\
    chdir c:\\public\\lewis
    copy c:*.* d:\\

If, instead, you want to copy all files in the \\PUBLIC\\JONES and
\\PUBLIC\\LEWIS directories to your current location on drive D, type the
following commands:

    chdir c:\\public\\jones
    copy c:*.* d:
    chdir c:\\public\\lewis
    copy c:*.* d:

