\i\bÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ\p

                              \bSMARTDRVÄÄNotes\p

\bUsing extended memory\p

For SMARTDrive to use extended memory, your CONFIG.SYS file must contain a
DEVICE command for HIMEM.SYS or another extended-memory manager that
conforms to the Lotus/Intel/Microsoft/AST eXtended Memory Specification
(XMS).

\bLoading SMARTDrive into the upper memory area\p

If the upper memory area is available through MS-DOS, SMARTDrive will
automatically load into upper memory. You do not need to use the LOADHIGH
command with SMARTDrive.

\bSMARTDrive and Compressed Drives\p

SMARTDrive does not actually cache compressed drives; instead, it caches the
physical drive on which the compressed volume file is located. This improves
the speed of both the physical drive and the compressed drive.

                                      
.context SMARTDRV--Example
.context @SMARTDRV--Example
:nSMARTDRV--Examples
:z3
\i\p\aSyntax\v@SMARTDRV\v\i\p  \i\p\aNotes\v@SMARTDRV--Note\v\i\p                                                           
\i\bÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ\p

                             \bSMARTDRVÄÄExamples\p

To create a SMARTDrive disk cache with a cache size of 256K (the default
size), add the following command to your AUTOEXEC.BAT file:

    c:\\dos\\smartdrv

\bExample: A typical SMARTDrive command\p

Suppose you want to create a disk cache with a cache size of 2048K, and
ensure that programs cannot reduce the size of the cache to less than 1024K.
To do this and to specify that the SMARTDRV.EXE file is located in the DOS
directory on drive C, add the following line to your AUTOEXEC.BAT file:

    c:\\dos\\smartdrv 2048 1024

\bExample: Enabling and disabling caching on specific drives\p

Suppose you want to disable all caching of your floppy-disk drives and
enable write caching on Interlnk drive D. (Interlnk drives, like floppy-disk
drives, are not write-cached because it's possible to lose access to the
drive before all information has been written from the cache). To do this,
you would add the following command to your AUTOEXEC.BAT:

    c:\\dos\\smartdrv a- b- d+

\bExample: Saving cached information on the hard disk\p

Before pressing your computer's reset button or turning off your computer,
it is a good idea to have SMARTDrive write all cached information from
memory to any cached disks. To do this, type the following at the command
prompt:

    smartdrv /c

You will not need to use this command before restarting your computer by
pressing the CTRL+ALT+DELETE keys: SMARTDrive detects the CTRL+ALT+DELETE
key sequence and automatically writes all information to cached disks before
allowing the system to restart.

